Additionally we need to make it clear that plan is not being built because there weren't any changes detected since the last build.

I have run into this issue a few times in Support tickets with evaluators not being able trigger builds for the first time.

Plan notification does not work for LDAP group when the account has different DN and sAMAccountName credential.
{code}
DN: CN=zed yap,OU=users,DC=atlassian,DC=net
sAMAccountName: zyap
{code}

The log will show the following:
{code}
2011-01-27 17:52:20,731 DEBUG [0-BAM::Events:pool-1-thread-15] [BasicResourcePool] trace com.mchange.v2.resourcepool.BasicResourcePool@379d2f6b [managed: 6, unused: 3, excluded: 0] (e.g. com.mchange.v2.c3p0.impl.NewPooledConnection@16a8c19b)
2011-01-27 17:52:20,732 DEBUG [0-BAM::Events:pool-1-thread-14] [LDAPStaticGroupAdaptor] found at least one group
2011-01-27 17:52:20,735 DEBUG [0-BAM::Events:pool-1-thread-14] [DefaultLDAPUserAdaptor] DefaultLDAPUserAdapter.search&(objectClass=person)(sAMAccountName=zed yap))
{code}

As the result of the LDAP serach filter which is construct from DN which lead the notification is not sent.

*NOTE:* This does not happens in user basis notification.

Artifact expiration on BEAC produces almost 500 000 lines of logs like
{noformat}
atlassian-bamboo.log.2:2011-01-30 08:34:33,143 INFO [QuartzScheduler_Worker-5] [BuildExpiryBean] Removing artifacts of CWD-TRUNKJIRAINT-420
atlassian-bamboo.log.2:2011-01-30 08:34:33,156 INFO [QuartzScheduler_Worker-5] [BuildExpiryBean] Removing artifacts of CWD-TRUNKJIRAINT-419
{noformat}

Priority of these messages should be decreased to debug to prevent log rotation which nukes the actually important logs.

This code
{code}
[@ww.select id="linesToDisplay" name="linesToDisplay" list=[10, 25, 50, 100] theme="simple"/]
{code}
and
{code}
public int getLinesToDisplay()
{
  return 25;
}
{code}
will not work as expected: generated dropdown list will not have "25" as initially selected value.

Problem is that webwork would internally use BigDecimal type and action method would return Integer and comparing them with method equal will always return false (see ContainUtil.contains(Object, Object)

